The paper deals with physical-layer security in a wireless network, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), and security (cs.CR). The use of multiple antennas and artificial noise also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed selection schemes for improving the achievable secrecy rate involve system-level optimization and decision-making, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
